   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Animal Assisted Therapy for Children in Guatemala</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Following the unexpected passing of our previous therapy dog, Mo&apos;os, the Fundacion Waibi donated a new therapy dog to Adisa. After five years of observed success with Mo&apos;os, we made the decision to continue with our Animal Assisted Therapy program. This project will allow us to pay the costs of assisted animal therapy sessions so that our new therapy dog, Argos, can provide weekly animal therapy to 20 children with disabilities in Santiago Atitlan.</narrative>
  </description>
